Ekiti State has recorded its first death from the COVID-19 pandemic, SaharaReporters has learnt. The deceased, a pregnant 29-year-old female community health worker based in Lagos, was said to have sneaked into Ekiti in spite the lockdown order in place. “Yes, a death has been recorded already, the third confirmed case. A pregnant woman who delivered her baby successfully, the baby is okay but she is dead,” a health worker told SaharaReporters. The state on Tuesday confirmed that a doctor working with a private clinic tested positive for the virus. According to Commissioner for Health in Ekiti, Dr Mojisola Yaya-Kolade, the doctor contracted the virus while treating the late pregnant wo